column4: Russian army troops opened fire on demonstrators in Riga, killing seventy-three and injuring two hundred people.
World War I: The war began.
Soviet occupation of Latvia in 1940: Soviet troops occupied the country.
Occupation of Latvia by Nazi Germany: Nazi troops occupied Riga.
Occupation of Latvia by Soviet Union 1944-1945: The Soviet army reentered Riga.
The Barricades: Pro-Communist political forces attempted to restore Soviet power in Latvia.
